@startuml

title Ideal User Inventory Item Request Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Frontend Website" as Frontend
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as Middleware
  participant "Controller" as Controller
  participant "Inventory Service" as Service
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as Database

note right of User
IMPORTANT: This sequence assumes normal system operation. If a failure
occurs at any layer, the system returns an error message
and prompts the user to retry. It is also assumed the User is
authenticated/authorized.
end note

== Search Inventory ==
User -> Frontend: Search inventory item
activate Frontend


Frontend -> Apache: Request /items
activate Apache
Apache -> Middleware: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate Middleware
Middleware -> Controller: Pass validated request
deactivate Middleware

activate Controller
Controller -> Service: getItems()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Retrieve items
activate ORM
ORM -> Database: SELECT * FROM items
activate Database
Database --> ORM: Item records
deactivate Database
ORM --> Service: Item collection
deactivate ORM

Service --> Controller: Item list
deactivate Service
Controller --> Frontend: Item list
deactivate Controller

Frontend --> User: Display inventory
deactivate Frontend


== Borrow Request ==
User -> Frontend: Select item & Request
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Apache: POST /borrowRequest
activate Apache
Apache -> Middleware: Forward request
deactivate Apache

activate Middleware
Middleware -> Controller: Pass validated request
deactivate Middleware

activate Controller
Controller -> Service: createBorrowRequest()
activate Service

Service -> ORM: Check item availability
activate ORM
ORM -> Database: SELECT status FROM items
activate Database
Database --> ORM: Item status
deactivate Database
ORM --> Service: Availability result
deactivate ORM

alt Item available

    Service -> ORM: Save borrow request
    activate ORM
    ORM -> Database: INSERT borrow_request
    activate Database
    Database --> ORM: Insert successful
    deactivate Database
    ORM --> Service: Request persisted
    deactivate ORM

    Service -> ORM: Update item status [Reserved]
    activate ORM
    ORM -> Database: UPDATE items SET status='Reserved'
    activate Database
    Database --> ORM: Update successful
    deactivate Database
    ORM --> Service: Status updated
    deactivate ORM

    Service --> Controller: Request approved

else Item unavailable

    Service --> Controller: Request rejected

end

deactivate Service
Controller --> Frontend: Response
deactivate Controller

Frontend --> User: Display confirmation
deactivate Frontend

@enduml